The study of '''Higher Education Leadership''' encompasses primarily the academic disciplines of leadership and organizational theory.

Founded in 1976, the Association for the Study of Higher Education (ASHE) is a national organization of scholars dedicated to higher education as a field of study. Relevant journals include the ''[[American Educational Research Association#Journals of AERA|American Educational Research Journal]]'' and ''[[Studies in Higher Education]]'' and ''Research in Higher Education''.

Many colleges and universities offer Ph.D. and Ed.D. programs in higher education administration and leadership, including [[Eastern Michigan University]].

