[[File:Samuel Sharpe by Matilda Sharpe.jpg|thumbnail|right|Matilda's portrait of her father, Samuel.]] '''Matilda Sharpe''' (4 April 1830 &ndash; 30 April 1916)<ref name=Oxf>[http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/article/51750 "Sharpe, Matilda (1830–1916)"] by Ruth Watts in ''[[Oxford Dictionary of National Biography]]'', online edition, [[Oxford University Press]], 2004. Retrieved 31 May 2014.</ref> was a British teacher, educational reformer and painter. In [[Highgate]], [[north London]], [[List of founders of English schools and colleges|she founded]] [[Channing School|Channing House School]]<ref>''[https://www.webcitation.org/6PzMGdmBH Memorials of Robert Spears 1825-99]''. Belfast: Ulster Unitarian Christian Association, p. 35.</ref> (after [[Robert Spears (minister)|Robert Spears']] idea) and a [[General Assembly of Unitarian and Free Christian Churches|Unitarian Chapel]] in Despard Road. She was the daughter of [[Samuel Sharpe (scholar)|Samuel Sharpe]].
Sharpe was a talented painter and several of her portraits are in the collection of the [[National Portrait Gallery, London|National Portrait Gallery]], London.<ref>[http://www.npg.org.uk/collections/search/person/mp07545/matilda-sharpe Matilda Sharpe (1830-1915)] National Portrait Gallery, 2014. Retrieved 31 May 2014.</ref>
