'''NLSPA''' ('''Nikki Lynam School of Performing Arts''') is a [[street dance]] [[Dance studio|school]] based in [[Rotherham]], [[South Yorkshire]], [[England]].  NLSPA was set up by Nikki Lynam in 2001.  This studio is well known in the United Kingdom through their ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]'' [[Britain's Got Talent (series 4)|2010 semi-finalist]] group ICE, and the Future Dance Group.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://thefuturedance.co.uk/group/our-dance-school-19 |title=Our dance school |publisher=Future Dance Group |accessdate=28 January 2013 }}</ref>  The NLSPA provides classes in [[singing]], [[drama]], [[gymnastics]], and street dances such as [[B-boying|breakdance]] and [[lyrical hip hop]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rotherham.gov.uk/info/838/arts-information_and_advice/402/arts_in_rotherham-dance/4 |title=Dance groups and classes in Rotherham |publisher=[[Metropolitan Borough of Rotherham|Rotherham Metropolitan Borough Council]] }}</ref>

